							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/pico-iyer/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/14177-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/14177-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Pico Iyer" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/pico-iyer/">Pico Iyer</a></h6>
										Pico Iyer is the author of fifteen books, translated into twenty-three languages, and has been a constant contributor for more than thirty years to <em>Time, The New York Times, Harper’s Magazine, the Los Angeles Times,</em> and more than 250 other periodicals worldwide. His four recent talks for TED have received more than eleven million views. His new book <em>The Half Known Life</em> is available now from Riverhead.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="http://www.picoiyerjourneys.com" target="_blank" class="external">http://www.picoiyerjourneys.com</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
					</div>
